#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.38"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.38:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.38:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.38:0.3"
msgid "38. Patilīnasutta"
msgstr "38. Withdrawn"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.41"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: Panuṇṇapaccekasacco → paṇunnapaccekasacco (?)
msgctxt "an4.38:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Panuṇṇapaccekasacco, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘samavayasaṭṭhesano "
"passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro patilīno’ti vuccati."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth, has totally given up searching, has stilled the physical process, and "
"is said to be ‘withdrawn’."

msgctxt "an4.38:1.2"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu panuṇṇapaccekasacco hoti?"
msgstr ""
"And how has a mendicant eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth?"

msgctxt "an4.38:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yāni tāni puthusamaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"puthupaccekasaccāni, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Different ascetics and brahmins have different idiosyncratic interpretations "
"of the truth. For example:"

# For tam jivan tam sariram, BB has “the same”. I used to have “identical”. However, one two things may be identical but not the same thing, eg. copies of a book. The point of this idiom is not that “the soul and the body are identical kinds of things” but that they are literally the same thing.
msgctxt "an4.38:1.4"
msgid ""
"sassato lokoti vā, asassato lokoti vā, antavā lokoti vā, anantavā lokoti vā, "
"taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīranti vā, aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīranti vā, hoti tathāgato "
"paraṃ maraṇāti vā, na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, hoti ca na ca hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti vā, neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇāti "
"vā;"
msgstr ""
"the world is eternal, or not eternal, or finite, or infinite; the soul and "
"the body are the same thing, or they are different things; after death, a "
"Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and doesn’t exist, or "
"neither exists nor doesn’t exist."

msgctxt "an4.38:1.5"
msgid ""
"sabbāni tāni nuṇṇāni honti panuṇṇāni cattāni vantāni muttāni pahīnāni "
"paṭinissaṭṭhāni."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant has dispelled, eliminated, thrown out, rejected, let go of, "
"given up, and relinquished all these."

msgctxt "an4.38:1.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu panuṇṇapaccekasacco hoti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the "
"truth."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:2.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant totally given up searching?"

msgctxt "an4.38:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno kāmesanā pahīnā hoti, bhavesanā pahīnā hoti, "
"brahmacariyesanā paṭippassaddhā."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they’ve given up searching for sensual pleasures, for continued "
"existence, and for a spiritual path."

msgctxt "an4.38:2.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu samavayasaṭṭhesano hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has totally given up searching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti?"
msgstr "And how has a mendicant stilled the physical process?"

msgctxt "an4.38:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and "
"sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or "
"pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness."

msgctxt "an4.38:3.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant has stilled the physical process."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu patilīno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant withdrawn?"

msgctxt "an4.38:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno asmimāno pahīno hoti ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato "
"anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr ""
"It’s when they’ve given up the conceit ‘I am’, cut it off at the root, made "
"it like a palm stump, obliterated it, so it’s unable to arise in the future."

msgctxt "an4.38:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu patilīno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is withdrawn."

msgctxt "an4.38:4.4"
msgid ""
"Panuṇṇapaccekasacco, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ‘samavayasaṭṭhesano "
"passaddhakāyasaṅkhāro patilīno’ti vuccatīti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant has eliminated idiosyncratic interpretations of the truth, has "
"totally given up searching, has stilled the physical process, and is said to "
"be ‘withdrawn’."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.42"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:5.1"
msgid "Kāmesanā bhavesanā,"
msgstr "The search for sensual pleasures, for a good rebirth,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:5.2"
msgid "brahmacariyesanā saha;"
msgstr "together with the search for a spiritual path;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:5.3"
msgid "Iti saccaparāmāso,"
msgstr "holding tight to the notion ‘this is the truth’,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:5.4"
msgid "diṭṭhiṭṭhānā samussayā."
msgstr "and the mass of grounds for views."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:6.1"
msgid "Sabbarāgavirattassa,"
msgstr "For one detached from all lusts,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:6.2"
msgid "taṇhakkhayavimuttino;"
msgstr "freed by the ending of craving,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:6.3"
msgid "Esanā paṭinissaṭṭhā,"
msgstr "searching has been relinquished,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:6.4"
msgid "diṭṭhiṭṭhānā samūhatā."
msgstr "and viewpoints eradicated."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.38:7.1"
msgid "Sa ve santo sato bhikkhu,"
msgstr "That mendicant is peaceful and mindful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:7.2"
msgid "passaddho aparājito;"
msgstr "a tranquil champion."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:7.3"
msgid "Mānābhisamayā buddho,"
msgstr "And when they’re awakened by comprehending conceit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.38:7.4"
msgid "patilīnoti vuccatī”ti."
msgstr "they’re called ‘withdrawn’.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.38:7.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
